<h2>Solar Incentives in Seattle</h2>
<p>Seattle residents can take advantage of the federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC), which provides a 30% tax credit on the total cost of solar panel installation through 2032. Washington State offers additional incentives including sales tax exemptions on solar equipment and the Renewable Energy Production Incentive, which has provided payments for solar energy production. Seattle Light participates in net metering programs, allowing customers to receive credit for excess energy their solar panels produce and feed back into the grid. Property owners should also note that solar panel installations are exempt from property tax increases in Washington State, meaning the added home value from solar panels won't increase your property taxes. Local rebates and financing options are periodically available through Seattle Light and regional energy efficiency programs.</p>

